values: Le plus grand marche au poisson du monde..mais comme c est au japon, ca ne sent meme pas la poiscaille..quel est le mystere? l arrivee des thon vers 4h est un moment surrealiste..on se croirait dans une fabrique d obus.
crazy like a tokyo tv show..
Myriam Mihindou a Haiti en compagnie d une troupe de theatre locale
ce monsieur a le visage sculpte par son instrument..
..enfin! je l ai eu! je l ai eu ma photo. Cet homme semble tout droit sorti d'un dessin anime de Miyasaki
Pic nic avec l'invasion des enfants perdus; je veux retrouver la vitalite de mes 8ans!
we went to Odaeba to see the nomad exhibition "ashes and snow"; fascinating!
In tokyo toy shops, you mostly see young highschool girls than children..
Train drivers are really...funny to watch. Sometimes they make noises and strange signs while they drive, alone in their boxes..codes in japan are quite disturbing sometimes :}
Indian classical music is like being alone in mountains, just next to gods and clouds. (concert's pic from a friend)
Little exhibition of illustrations and paintings at the top of the huuuge sony building of Ginza. Those from Kana Ootsuki where the best!
..weird place, the bridge next to yoyogi parc. On sundays, all weirdest stylish people come and just wait to be pictured, for nothing, just like animal circus. Why not..
zooom Live advertisement...the guy staid in this harajuku street the all day, dancing and screaming to invite us in whatever restaurant...who cared?
..I left tokyo with lovely people in my heart *snif*
King dinesh in his palace :) Tasted the best mango rhum cocktail ever!

There were tama's huge art university open days, it was really impressive! The painting section was the most interesting part, those paintings are big like walls...I still don t know how but i lost almost all my pictures of this day..i must have deleted all my memory card without saving the pictures. Fooly me ><
each boxes is for a different artist!
tried some clothes in recycle shops :)
We saw Fuji san from enoshima..but it s only in my eyes!
